    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-29T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-29T15:00:00-05:00" n="38"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d38">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.51/238a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-29T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 29, 1917, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1806. Your 1904, October 24, 7 p.m. Rumored cession of Kamchatka Peninsula to
                    United States for Rs. 20,000,000 [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] without any
                    foundation whatsoever. United States has arranged certain loans and credits with
                    free Russia founded exclusively on credit of Russian Government and for the
                    single purpose of cooperating in our common struggle against the autocratic
                    militarism of Germany. The President has already announced to the world that the
                    United States has no desire to add to its own territory.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
